#: l10n/source/edge.xml:208
msgid "Additional resources"
msgstr "其他资源"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:209
msgid ""
"The SUSE Edge for Telco Documentation (<xref linkend=\"atip\"/>) has "
"examples of more advanced usage of Metal<superscript>3</superscript> for "
"telco use-cases."
msgstr ""
"SUSE Edge for Telco 文档（<xref linkend=\"atip\"/>）提供了 "
"Metal<superscript>3</superscript> 在电信领域使用场景中更高级的用法示例。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:210
msgid "Single-node configuration"
msgstr "单节点配置"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:211
msgid ""
"For test/PoC environments where the management cluster is a single node, it "
"is possible to avoid the requirement for an additional floating IP managed "
"via MetalLB."
msgstr "对于管理群集仅包含单个节点的测试/PoC 环境，可能不需要通过 MetalLB "
"管理额外的浮动 IP。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:212
msgid ""
"In this mode, the endpoint for the management cluster APIs is the IP of the "
"management cluster, therefore it should be reserved when using DHCP or "
"statically configured to ensure the management cluster IP does not change - "
"referred to as <literal>&lt;MANAGEMENT_CLUSTER_IP&gt;</literal> below."
msgstr ""
"在此模式下，管理群集 API 的端点是管理群集的 IP，因此在使用 DHCP 时应预留该 "
"IP，或者配置静态 IP，以确保管理群集 IP 不会变化 - 在下面显示为 "
"<literal>MANAGEMENT_CLUSTER_IP</literal>。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:213
msgid ""
"To enable this scenario, the Metal<superscript>3</superscript> chart values "
"required are as follows:"
msgstr "为了实现此方案，必须如下所示指定 Metal<superscript>3</superscript> chart 值："

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:214
msgid "Disabling TLS for virtualmedia ISO attachment"
msgstr "对虚拟媒体 ISO 挂接禁用 TLS"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:215
msgid ""
"Some server vendors verify the SSL connection when attaching virtual-media "
"ISO images to the BMC, which can cause a problem because the generated "
"certificates for the Metal<superscript>3</superscript> deployment are self-"
"signed, to work around this issue it’s possible to disable TLS only for the "
"virtualmedia disk attachment with Metal<superscript>3</superscript> chart "
"values as follows:"
msgstr ""
"某些服务器供应商在将虚拟媒体 ISO 映像挂接到 BMC 时会验证 SSL "
"连接，这可能会导致出现问题，因为针对 Metal<superscript>3</superscript> "
"部署生成的证书是自我签名证书。要解决此问题，可以使用如下所示的 "
"Metal<superscript>3</superscript> chart 值仅对虚拟媒体磁盘挂接禁用 TLS："

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:216
msgid ""
"An alternative solution is to configure the BMCs with the CA cert - in this "
"case you can read the certificates from the cluster using <literal>kubectl</"
"literal>:"
msgstr ""
"另一种解决方法是使用 CA 证书配置 BMC - 在这种情况下，可以使用 "
"<literal>kubectl</literal> 从群集读取证书："

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:217
msgid ""
"The certificate can then be configured on the server BMC console, although "
"the process for that is vendor specific (and not possible for all vendors, "
"in which case the <literal>enable_vmedia_tls</literal> flag may be required)."
msgstr ""
"然后可以在服务器 BMC "
"控制台上配置证书，不过，配置过程因供应商而异（并且不一定适用于所有供应商，如"
"果不适用，可能需要指定 <literal>enable_vmedia_tls</literal> 标志）。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:218
msgid "Remote host onboarding with Elemental"
msgstr "使用 Elemental 进行远程主机接入"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:219
msgid ""
"This section documents the \"phone home network provisioning\" solution as "
"part of SUSE Edge, where we use Elemental to assist with node onboarding. "
"Elemental is a software stack enabling remote host registration and "
"centralized full cloud-native OS management with Kubernetes. In the SUSE "
"Edge stack we use the registration feature of Elemental to enable remote "
"host onboarding into Rancher so that hosts can be integrated into a "
"centralized management platform and from there, deploy and manage Kubernetes "
"clusters along with layered components, applications, and their lifecycle, "
"all from a common place."
msgstr ""
"本章介绍 SUSE Edge 中的“自主回连网络置备”解决方案。我们将使用 Elemental "
"来协助完成节点接入。Elemental 是一个软件堆栈，可用于注册远程主机和通过 "
"Kubernetes 实现集中式云原生操作系统全面管理。在 SUSE Edge 堆栈中，我们将使用 "
"Elemental 的注册功能将远程主机接入 Rancher，以便将主机集成到集中式管理平台，"
"然后从该平台部署和管理 Kubernetes "
"群集以及分层组件、应用程序及其生命周期，所有这些操作都在一个中心位置完成。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:220
msgid ""
"This approach can be useful in scenarios where the devices that you want to "
"control are not on the same network as the management cluster or do not have "
"a out-of-band management controller onboard to allow more direct control, "
"and where you’re booting many different \"unknown\" systems at the edge, and "
"need to securely onboard and manage them at scale. This is a common scenario "
"for use cases in retail, industrial IoT, or other spaces where you have "
"little control over the network your devices are being installed in."
msgstr ""
"此方法在以下情况下可能很有用：您要控制的设备与管理群集不在同一网络中，或没有"
"带外管理控制器接入功能可以进行更直接的控制；您要在边缘处引导许多不同的“未知”"
"系统，并且需要安全地大规模接入和管理这些系统。这种情况在以下领域的使用场景中"
"很常见：零售、工业物联网，或几乎无法通过设备要安装到的网络进行控制的其他领域"
"。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><informalfigure><mediaobject>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:222
msgid ""
"<imageobject> <imagedata fileref=\"quickstart-elemental-architecture.svg\" "
"width=\"\"/> </imageobject>"
msgstr ""
"<imageobject> <imagedata fileref=\"quickstart-elemental-architecture.svg\" "
"width=\"\"/> </imageobject>"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><informalfigure><mediaobject><textobject><phrase>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:223
msgid "quickstart elemental architecture"
msgstr "Elemental 体系结构快速入门"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:224
msgid "Resources needed"
msgstr "所需资源"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:225
msgid ""
"The following describes the minimum system and environmental requirements to "
"run through this quickstart:"
msgstr "下面说明了学习本快速入门所要满足的最低系统和环境要求："

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:226
msgid ""
"A host for the centralized management cluster (the one hosting Rancher and "
"Elemental):"
msgstr "集中式管理群集的主机（托管 Rancher 和 Elemental 的主机）："

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:227
msgid ""
"Minimum 8 GB RAM and 20 GB disk space for development or testing (see <link "
"xl:href=\"https://ranchermanager.docs.rancher.com/v2.10/getting-started/"
"installation-and-upgrade/installation-requirements#hardware-"
"requirements\">here</link> for production use)"
msgstr ""
"至少 8 GB RAM 和 20 GB 磁盘空间，用于开发或测试（对于生产用途，请参见<link "
"xl:href=\"https://ranchermanager.docs.rancher.com/v2.10/getting-started/"
"installation-and-upgrade/installation-requirements#hardware-requirements\""
">此处</link>）"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:228
msgid ""
"A target node to be provisioned, i.e. the edge device (a virtual machine can "
"be used for demoing or testing purposes)"
msgstr "要置备的目标节点，即边缘设备（可以使用虚拟机进行演示或测试）"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:229
msgid "Minimum 4GB RAM, 2 CPU cores, and 20 GB disk"
msgstr "至少 4GB RAM、2 个 CPU 核心和 20 GB 磁盘空间"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:230
msgid ""
"A resolvable host name for the management cluster or a static IP address to "
"use with a service like sslip.io"
msgstr "管理群集的可解析主机名，或用于 sslip.io 等服务的静态 IP 地址"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:231
msgid "A host to build the installation media via Edge Image Builder"
msgstr "用于通过 Edge Image Builder 构建安装媒体的主机"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:232
msgid ""
"Running SLES 15 SP6, openSUSE Leap 15.6, or another compatible operating "
"system that supports Podman."
msgstr "运行 SLES 15 SP6、openSUSE Leap 15.6 或其他支持 Podman 的兼容操作系统。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:233
msgid ""
"With <link xl:href=\"https://kubernetes.io/docs/reference/kubectl/kubectl/"
"\">Kubectl</link>, <link xl:href=\"https://podman.io\">Podman</link>, and "
"<link xl:href=\"https://helm.sh\">Helm</link> installed"
msgstr ""
"已安装 <link xl:href="
"\"https://kubernetes.io/docs/reference/kubectl/kubectl/\">Kubectl</link>、"
"<link xl:href=\"https://podman.io\">Podman</link> 和 <link xl:href="
"\"https://helm.sh\">Helm</link>"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:234
msgid "A USB flash drive to boot from (if using physical hardware)"
msgstr "用于引导的 USB 闪存盘（如果使用物理硬件）"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:235
msgid ""
"A downloaded copy of the latest SUSE Linux Micro 6.0 SelfInstall \"GM2\" ISO "
"image found <link xl:href=\"https://www.suse.com/download/sle-micro/\">here</"
"link>."
msgstr ""
"下载的最新 SUSE Linux Micro 6.0 自安装“GM2”ISO 映像，该映像可在<link xl:href="
"\"https://www.suse.com/download/sle-micro/\">此处</link>获取。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><note><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:236
msgid ""
"Existing data found on target machines will be overwritten as part of the "
"process, please make sure you backup any data on any USB storage devices and "
"disks attached to target deployment nodes."
msgstr "在初始配置过程中会重写目标计算机上的现有数据，"
"因此请务必备份挂接到目标部署节点的所有 USB 存储设备和磁盘上的所有数据。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:237
msgid ""
"This guide is created using a Digital Ocean droplet to host the upstream "
"cluster and an Intel NUC as the downstream device. For building the "
"installation media, SUSE Linux Enterprise Server is used."
msgstr ""
"本指南是使用托管上游群集的 Digital Ocean droplet 以及用作下游设备的 Intel "
"NUC 制作的。为了构建安装媒体，我们使用了 SUSE Linux Enterprise Server。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:238
msgid "Build bootstrap cluster"
msgstr "构建引导群集"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:239
msgid ""
"Start by creating a cluster capable of hosting Rancher and Elemental. This "
"cluster needs to be routable from the network that the downstream nodes are "
"connected to."
msgstr "首先创建一个能够托管 Rancher 和 Elemental "
"的群集。必须可以从下游节点所连接到的网络路由此群集。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:240
msgid "Create Kubernetes cluster"
msgstr "创建 Kubernetes 群集"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:241
msgid ""
"If you are using a hyperscaler (such as Azure, AWS or Google Cloud), the "
"easiest way to set up a cluster is using their built-in tools. For the sake "
"of conciseness in this guide, we do not detail the process of each of these "
"options."
msgstr ""
"如果您使用的是超大规模云（例如 Azure、AWS 或 Google "
"Cloud），那么，设置群集的最简单方法是使用这些云的内置工具。为简洁起见，本指南"
"不会详细介绍使用每种选项的操作过程。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:242
msgid ""
"If you are installing onto bare-metal or another hosting service where you "
"need to also provide the Kubernetes distribution itself, we recommend using "
"<link xl:href=\"https://docs.rke2.io/install/quickstart\">RKE2</link>."
msgstr ""
"如果您要安装到裸机或其他宿主服务，同时需要提供 Kubernetes 发行版本身，"
"我们建议您使用 <link xl:href=\"https://docs.rke2.io/install/quickstart\""
">RKE2</link>。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:243
msgid "Set up DNS"
msgstr "设置 DNS"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:244
msgid ""
"Before continuing, you need to set up access to your cluster. As with the "
"setup of the cluster itself, how you configure DNS will be different "
"depending on where it is being hosted."
msgstr "在继续之前，需要设置群集访问权限。与群集本身的设置一样，DNS "
"的配置方式因群集的托管位置而异。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><tip><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:245
msgid ""
"If you do not want to handle setting up DNS records (for example, this is "
"just an ephemeral test server), you can use a service like <link xl:"
"href=\"https://sslip.io\">sslip.io</link> instead. With this service, you "
"can resolve any IP address with <literal>&lt;address&gt;.sslip.io</literal>."
msgstr ""
"如果您不想处理 DNS 记录的设置（例如，这只是一个临时使用的测试服务器），"
"可以改用 <link xl:href=\"https://sslip.io\">sslip.io</link> "
"之类的服务。通过此服务，可以使用 <literal>&lt;address&gt;.sslip.io</literal> "
"解析任何 IP 地址。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:247
msgid ""
"To install Rancher, you need to get access to the Kubernetes API of the "
"cluster you just created. This looks different depending on what "
"distribution of Kubernetes is being used."
msgstr "要安装 Rancher，需要访问刚刚创建的群集的 Kubernetes API。具体方式因使用的 "
"Kubernetes 发行版而异。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:248
msgid ""
"For RKE2, the kubeconfig file will have been written to <literal>/etc/"
"rancher/rke2/rke2.yaml</literal>.  Save this file as <literal>~/.kube/"
"config</literal> on your local system.  You may need to edit the file to "
"include the correct externally routable IP address or host name."
msgstr ""
"对于 RKE2，kubeconfig 文件会写入 <literal>/etc/rancher/rke2/"
"rke2.yaml</literal>。将此文件作为 <literal>~/.kube/config</literal> "
"保存在本地系统上。可能需要编辑该文件，以包含正确的外部可路由 IP "
"地址或主机名。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:249
msgid ""
"Install Rancher easily with the commands from the <link xl:href=\"https://"
"ranchermanager.docs.rancher.com/v2.10/getting-started/installation-and-"
"upgrade/install-upgrade-on-a-kubernetes-cluster\">Rancher Documentation</"
"link>:"
msgstr ""
"使用 <link xl:href=\"https://ranchermanager.docs.rancher.com/v2.10/"
"getting-started/installation-and-upgrade/install-upgrade-on-a-kubernetes-"
"cluster\">Rancher 文档</link>中所述的命令轻松安装 Rancher："

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:250
msgid "Install <link xl:href=\"https://cert-manager.io\">cert-manager</link>:"
msgstr "安装 <link xl:href=\"https://cert-manager.io\">cert-manager</link>："

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:251
msgid "Then install Rancher itself:"
msgstr "然后安装 Rancher 本身："

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><note><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:252
msgid ""
"If this is intended to be a production system, please use cert-manager to "
"configure a real certificate (such as one from Let’s Encrypt)."
msgstr "如果目标系统是生产系统，请使用 cert-manager 配置实际证书（例如 Let's Encrypt "
"提供的证书）。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:253
msgid ""
"Browse to the host name you set up and log in to Rancher with the "
"<literal>bootstrapPassword</literal> you used. You will be guided through a "
"short setup process."
msgstr ""
"浏览到您设置的主机名，然后使用您的 <literal>bootstrapPassword</literal> "
"登录到 Rancher。系统将指导您完成一个简短的设置过程。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:254
msgid "Install Elemental"
msgstr "安装 Elemental"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:255
msgid ""
"With Rancher installed, you can now install the Elemental operator and "
"required CRD’s. The Helm chart for Elemental is published as an OCI artifact "
"so the installation is a little simpler than other charts.  It can be "
"installed from either the same shell you used to install Rancher or in the "
"browser from within Rancher’s shell."
msgstr ""
"安装 Rancher 后，接下来可以安装 Elemental Operator 和所需的 CRD。Elemental "
"的 Helm chart 作为 OCI 制品发布，因此其安装过程比其他 chart 略简单一些。"
"可以通过您用来安装 Rancher 的同一外壳安装 Helm chart，也可以在浏览器中通过 "
"Rancher 的外壳安装。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:256
msgid "(Optionally) Install the Elemental UI extension"
msgstr "（可选）安装 Elemental UI 扩展"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:257
msgid ""
"To use the Elemental UI, log in to your Rancher instance, click the three-"
"line menu in the upper left:"
msgstr "要使用 Elemental UI，请登录到您的 Rancher 实例，单击左上角的三线菜单："

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><informalfigure><mediaobject>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:258
msgid ""
"<imageobject> <imagedata fileref=\"installing-elemental-extension-1.png\" "
"width=\"\"/> </imageobject>"
msgstr ""
