msgid "Now, the only thing left is to create the network and start it:"
msgstr "现在，唯一剩下的操作就是创建并启动网络："

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1415
msgid "Base Directory Configuration"
msgstr "基础目录配置"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1416
msgid ""
"The base directory configuration is the same across all different "
"components, so we will set it up here."
msgstr "基础目录配置在所有组件中都相同，现在我们就设置此配置。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1417
msgid "We will first create the necessary subdirectories:"
msgstr "首先创建所需的子目录："

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1418
msgid ""
"Make sure to add whichever base image you plan to use into the <literal>base-"
"images</literal> directory. This guide will focus on the Self Install ISO "
"found <link xl:href=\"https://www.suse.com/download/sle-micro/\">here</link>."
msgstr ""
"请确保将您要使用的任何基础映像添加到 <literal>base-images</literal> 目录中。"
"本指南将重点介绍<link xl:href=\"https://www.suse.com/download/sle-micro/\""
">此处</link>提供的自安装 ISO 映像。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1419
msgid "Let’s copy the downloaded image:"
msgstr "我们来复制已下载的映像："

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><note><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1420
msgid "EIB is never going to modify the base image input."
msgstr "EIB 永远不会修改基础映像输入。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1421
msgid "Let’s create a file containing the desired network configuration:"
msgstr "我们来创建一个包含所需网络配置的文件："

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1422
msgid ""
"This configuration ensures the following are present on the provisioned "
"systems (using the specified MAC address):"
msgstr "此配置确保置备的系统上存在以下设置（使用指定的 MAC 地址）："

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1423
msgid "an Ethernet interface with a static IP address"
msgstr "采用静态 IP 地址的以太网接口"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1424
msgid "routing"
msgstr "路由"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1425
msgid "DNS"
msgstr "DNS"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1426
msgid "hostname (<literal>host1.local</literal>)"
msgstr "主机名 (<literal>host1.local</literal>)"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1427
msgid "The resulting file structure should now look like:"
msgstr "最终的文件结构现在应如下所示："

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1428
msgid "Base Definition File"
msgstr "基础定义文件"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1429
msgid ""
"Edge Image Builder is using <emphasis>definition files</emphasis> to modify "
"the SUSE Linux Micro images. These files contain the majority of "
"configurable options.  Many of these options will be repeated across the "
"different component sections, so we will list and explain those here."
msgstr ""
"Edge Image Builder 使用<emphasis>定义文件</emphasis>来修改 SUSE Linux Micro "
"映像。这些文件包含大部分可配置选项。其中的许多选项将在不同的组件部分中重复出"
"现，因此下面列出并解释了这些选项。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><tip><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1430
msgid ""
"Full list of customization options in the definition file can be found in "
"the <link xl:href=\"https://github.com/suse-edge/edge-image-builder/blob/"
"release-1.1/docs/building-images.md#image-definition-file\">upstream "
"documentation</link>"
msgstr ""
"定义文件中自定义选项的完整列表可以在<link xl:href=\"https://github.com/"
"suse-edge/edge-image-builder/blob/release-1.1/docs/building-images.md#image-"
"definition-file\">上游文档</link>中找到"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1431
msgid ""
"We will take a look at the following fields which will be present in all "
"definition files:"
msgstr "我们来看看所有定义文件中的以下字段："

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1432
msgid ""
"The <literal>image</literal> section is required, and it specifies the input "
"image, its architecture and type, as well as what the output image will be "
"called."
msgstr "<literal>image</literal> "
"部分是必需的，用于指定输入映像、输入映像的体系结构和类型，以及输出映像的名称"
"。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1433
msgid ""
"The <literal>operatingSystem</literal> section is optional, and contains "
"configuration to enable login on the provisioned systems with the "
"<literal>root/eib</literal> username/password."
msgstr ""
"<literal>operatingSystem</literal> 部分是可选的，其中包含的配置允许用户通过 "
"<literal>root/eib</literal> 用户名/口令登录到置备的系统。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1434
msgid ""
"The <literal>kubernetes</literal> section is optional, and it defines the "
"Kubernetes type and version. We are going to use the RKE2 distribution. Use "
"<literal>kubernetes.version: v1.31.7+k3s1</literal> if K3s is desired "
"instead. Unless explicitly configured via the <literal>kubernetes.nodes</"
"literal> field, all clusters we bootstrap in this guide will be single-node "
"ones."
msgstr ""
"<literal>kubernetes</literal> 部分是可选的，用于定义 Kubernetes 类型和版本。"
"我们将使用 RKE2 发行版。如果需要 K3s，请改用 <literal>kubernetes.version: "
"v1.31.7+k3s1</literal>。除非通过 <literal>kubernetes.nodes</literal> "
"字段明确配置，否则本指南中引导的所有群集都是单节点群集。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1435
msgid ""
"The <literal>embeddedArtifactRegistry</literal> section will include all "
"images which are only referenced and pulled at runtime for the specific "
"component."
msgstr "<literal>embeddedArtifactRegistry</literal> "
"部分包含仅在运行时为特定组件引用和提取的所有映像。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1436
msgid "Rancher Installation"
msgstr "Rancher 安装"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><note><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1437
msgid ""
"The Rancher (<xref linkend=\"components-rancher\"/>) deployment that will be "
"demonstrated will be highly slimmed down for demonstration purposes. For "
"your actual deployments, additional artifacts may be necessary depending on "
"your configuration."
msgstr ""
"为便于演示，我们将大幅精简演示用的 Rancher（<xref linkend=\"components-"
"rancher\"/>）部署。对于实际部署，可能需要根据您的配置添加其他制品。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1438
msgid ""
"The <link xl:href=\"https://github.com/rancher/rancher/releases/tag/"
"v2.10.3\">Rancher 2.10.3</link> release assets contain a <literal>rancher-"
"images.txt</literal> file which lists all the images required for an air-"
"gapped installation."
msgstr ""
"<link xl:href=\"https://github.com/rancher/rancher/releases/tag/v2.10.3\""
">Rancher 2.10.3</link> 版本资产包含 <literal>rancher-images.txt</literal> "
"文件，其中列出了隔离式安装所需的所有映像。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1439
msgid ""
"There are over 600 container images in total which means that the resulting "
"CRB image would be roughly 30GB. For our Rancher installation, we will strip "
"down that list to the smallest working configuration. From there, you can "
"add back any images you may need for your deployments."
msgstr ""
"总共有超过 600 个容器映像，这意味着生成的 CRB 映像的大小约为 30GB。"
"对于我们的 Rancher "
"安装，我们将精简该列表，使之与最小有效配置相当。您可以在该列表中重新添加部署"
"所需的任何映像。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1440
msgid ""
"We will create the definition file and include the stripped down image list:"
msgstr "创建定义文件并在其中包含精简的映像列表："

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1441
msgid ""
"As compared to the full list of 600+ container images, this slimmed down "
"version only contains ~60 which makes the new CRB image only about 7GB."
msgstr "与包含 600 多个容器映像的完整列表相比，此精简版本仅包含约 60 个容器映像，"
"因此新 CRB 映像的大小只有大约 7GB。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1442
msgid "We also need to create a Helm values file for Rancher:"
msgstr "我们还需要为 Rancher 创建 Helm values 文件："

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><warning><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1443
msgid ""
"Setting the <literal>systemDefaultRegistry</literal> to <literal>registry."
"rancher.com</literal> allows Rancher to automatically look for images in the "
"embedded artifact registry started within the CRB image at boot. Omitting "
"this field may result in failure to find the container images on the node."
msgstr ""
"将 <literal>systemDefaultRegistry</literal> 设置为 "
"<literal>registry.rancher.com</literal> 可让 Rancher 在引导时，在 CRB "
"映像内启动的嵌入式制品注册表中自动查找映像。省略此字段可能会导致无法在节点上"
"找到容器映像。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1446
msgid ""
"Once a node using the built image is provisioned, we can verify the Rancher "
"installation:"
msgstr "置备使用构建映像的节点后，可以校验 Rancher 安装："

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1447 l10n/source/edge.xml:1458
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1465 l10n/source/edge.xml:1472
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1474
msgid ""
"The output should be similar to the following, showing that everything has "
"been successfully deployed:"
msgstr "输出应类似于以下内容，这表明已成功部署所有组件："

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1448
msgid ""
"And when we go to <literal>https://192.168.100.50.sslip.io</literal> and log "
"in with the <literal>adminadminadmin</literal> password that we set earlier, "
"we are greeted with the Rancher dashboard:"
msgstr ""
"当我们访问 <literal>https://192.168.100.50.sslip.io</literal> "
"并使用先前设置的 <literal>adminadminadmin</literal> 口令登录后，Rancher "
"仪表板即会显示："

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><informalfigure><mediaobject>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1449
msgid ""
"<imageobject> <imagedata fileref=\"air-gapped-rancher.png\" width=\"\"/> </"
"imageobject>"
msgstr ""
"<imageobject> <imagedata fileref=\"air-gapped-rancher.png\" width=\"\"/> "
"</imageobject>"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><informalfigure><mediaobject><textobject><phrase>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1450
msgid "air gapped rancher"
msgstr "隔离式 Rancher"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1451
msgid "SUSE Security Installation"
msgstr "SUSE Security 安装"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1452
msgid ""
"Unlike the Rancher installation, the SUSE Security installation does not "
"require any special handling in EIB. EIB will automatically air-gap every "
"image required by its underlying component NeuVector."
msgstr ""
"与 Rancher 安装不同，SUSE Security 安装不需要在 EIB 中进行任何特殊处理。EIB "
"将自动隔离底层组件 NeuVector 所需的每个映像。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1453
msgid "We will create the definition file:"
msgstr "创建定义文件："

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1454
msgid "We will also create a Helm values file for NeuVector:"
msgstr "另外，为 NeuVector 创建 Helm 值文件："

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1457
msgid ""
"Once a node using the built image is provisioned, we can verify the SUSE "
"Security installation:"
msgstr "置备使用构建映像的节点后，可以校验 SUSE Security 安装："

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1459
msgid "SUSE Storage Installation"
msgstr "SUSE Storage 安装"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1460
msgid ""
"The <link xl:href=\"https://longhorn.io/docs/1.7.3/deploy/install/airgap/"
"\">official documentation</link> for Longhorn contains a <literal>longhorn-"
"images.txt</literal> file which lists all the images required for an air-"
"gapped installation.  We will be including their mirrored counterparts from "
"the Rancher container registry in our definition file.  Let’s create it:"
msgstr ""
"Longhorn 的<link xl:href="
"\"https://longhorn.io/docs/1.7.3/deploy/install/airgap/\">官方文档</"
"link>包含 <literal>longhorn-images.txt</literal> "
"文件，其中列出了物理隔离式安装所需的所有映像。我们将在定义文件中包含它们的 "
"Rancher 容器注册表镜像副本。现在来创建此文件："

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><note><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1461
msgid ""
"You will notice that the definition file lists the <literal>open-iscsi</"
"literal> package. This is necessary since Longhorn relies on a "
"<literal>iscsiadm</literal> daemon running on the different nodes to provide "
"persistent volumes to Kubernetes."
msgstr ""
"您会注意到，定义文件列出了 <literal>open-iscsi</literal> "
"软件包。该软件包是必需的组件，因为 Longhorn 依赖于不同节点上运行的 "
"<literal>iscsiadm</literal> 守护程序来为 Kubernetes 提供持久性卷。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1464
msgid ""
"Once a node using the built image is provisioned, we can verify the Longhorn "
"installation:"
msgstr "置备使用构建映像的节点后，可以校验 Longhorn 安装："

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1466
msgid "KubeVirt and CDI Installation"
msgstr "KubeVirt 和 CDI 安装"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1467
msgid ""
"The Helm charts for both KubeVirt and CDI are only installing their "
"respective operators.  It is up to the operators to deploy the rest of the "
"systems which means we will have to include all necessary container images "
"in our definition file. Let’s create it:"
msgstr ""
"KubeVirt 和 CDI 的 Helm chart "
"只会安装各自的操作器。系统的其余组件将由操作器来部署，这意味着，我们必须在定"
"义文件中包含所有必要的容器映像。我们来创建定义文件："

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1470
msgid ""
"Once a node using the built image is provisioned, we can verify the "
"installation of both KubeVirt and CDI."
msgstr "置备使用构建映像的节点后，可以校验 KubeVirt 和 CDI 的安装。"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1471
msgid "Verify KubeVirt:"
msgstr "校验 KubeVirt："

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1473
msgid "Verify CDI:"
msgstr "校验 CDI："

